Ansible Class -01

TOPIC: ANSIBLE INTRODUCTION, ARCHITECTURE MASTER-SLAVE CONNECTION & PLAYBOOK
=================================================================================


We will use configuration management tool called as Ansible

Ansible alternate tools are chef, puppet most commonly companies used Ansible only

First we need to know the Ansible Architecture

Launch an EC2-Instance--------> no.of Instance:04---->1.Ansible Mster 2.Slave(Dev-server) 3.Slave(Test-server) 4.Slave(Prod-server)--------> instance 
type:t3.micro-------> with keypair-----> MySecuritygrp------> 8gb ebs -----> ok

Launch and connect 4 Instances

do all configuration in all 4 servers like below

hostnamectl set-hostname "ANSIBLE-MASTER"
hostnamectl set-hostname "DEV-SERVER"
hostnamectl set-hostname "TEST-SERVER"
hostnamectl set-hostname "PROD-SERVER"

First install Ansible on Ansible server

yum install ansible -y------------------> command to install Ansible tool

Ansible dependencies is Python and related to Python PIP(PIP means Python Install Package Module)

yum install python-pip -y---------------> command to install python-pip

As of now we done are launched 4 servers, Installed Ansible and dependencies python & python-pip on Ansible server

Now we need to do configuration on rest of the 3 servers are like below

1. need to set password for root user
2. need to do authenticate password update
3. need to restart sshd

need to do those 3 above steps on rest of 3 servers

passwd root
give password here

[root@DEV-SERVER ~]# passwd root
