Now we will start sriting Ansible Playbooks

Ansible Playbook consists of 3 sections

1.Traget section--------> means in which server we need to do
2.tasks section --------> means need to install/uninstall or update
3.variable section -----> means need to be store variables

we need to use for saving the ansible playbook with extension yml or yaml

yet another markup language

every yaml file starts with --- & ends with ...

installpresent
uninstall=absent
update=latest
start=started
stop=stopped
restart=restarted

[root@ANSIBLE-MASTER ~]# vim myfirstplaybook.yml

---
- hosts: dev
  connection: ssh
  
  task:
    - name: i am installing git on dev env
      yum: name=git state=present
... 

